<br>
EDIT: Forgot to mention, and I think it's already been stated that copyright licensing protects the USE of copyrighted information.  Which is why whether something being legal or not depends on it's useage.  Can you write cocacola on a piece of paper? yes, but you can't slap it on a product and sell it.  By the same token, you can write 0's and 1's till you are blue in the face, but if you play them in mp3 format without being licensed to do so, you are breaking the law.<br>
