Your metaphysical babbling is irrelavent.  What is relavent (and the ONLY thing relavent in this case) is whether the copy is in a tangible form or not.  In the case of a song stuck in your mind, it may seem very tangible to you but I assure you, the rest of the world does not consider it tangible.<br>
<br>
In the case of a song stored on a harddrive, that harddrive is a tangible medium and the copy is in a tangible form, therefore the latter is in violation of copyright laws.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I did not say, &quot;grab it and not pay.&quot; I said &quot;take down a technical schematic&quot; as in whip out paper and pencil, or my laptop, or whatever and scribble down a schematic.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Irrelavent again.<br>
If the material is copyrighted, the right to copy it or create derivative works from it is reserved for only the author.  That means, by scribbling it down on paper, you're reproducing the material in a tangible form and therefore it's in violation of copyright.<br>
<br>
Again, going back to your metaphysical nonsense, if you memorized that schematic and *never* write it down in any form whatsoever (whether it be on paper or on a computer harddrive), you are not in violation of reproducing a copyrighted material.<br>
<br>
However, the moment you create something from the schematic you've memorized, you're in violation of creating derivative works from copyrighted material.<br>
<br>
For more information, I recommend heading to www.whatiscopyright.org and reading up on the subject. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hayzen>Hayzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 726<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/10/03 1:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=865.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~digitalfoenix/shippou.jpg height=43 width=59></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RIAA files hundreds of cases against Music Swappers. </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What is relavent (and the ONLY thing relavent in this case) is whether the copy is in a tangible form or not. In the case of a song stuck in your mind, it may seem very tangible to you but I assure you, the rest of the world does not consider it tangible.<br>
<br>
In the case of a song stored on a harddrive, that harddrive is a tangible medium and the copy is in a tangible form, therefore the latter is in violation of copyright laws.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm certain I went over this already.  I acknowledge the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>law</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> says it is stealing.  However, I do not believe that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>law</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is always correct, nor do I believe that the law is final arbiter on what I consider ethically right or wrong, which is at the crux of the discussion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolvar>Wolvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>My third character is Lovawr</span><br>  Posts: 2382<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/10/03 2:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=865.topic&index=60>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RIAA files hundreds of cases against Music Swappers. </span><hr size=1> It wasn't a personal attack Hayzen, ignorance is not a slur... and it was hilarious. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
